               <msContents>
                  <summary>Letter from Lysimachos to Leontiskos, Thymos, and Tesenouphis, who had formed a company of fruit-pickers, about 13 talents that they had to pay as rent upon the orchard of Eirene and as another debt to the goverment for which Harpalos was their surety</summary>
                  <msItemStruct>
                     <note type="general">7 lines written along the fibers; on the back there are the address and the docket, written across the fibers</note>
                     <note type="general">The hand is formal and chancery</note>
                     <note type="general">The docket is written in a smaller hand by a clerk of the firm of Leontiskos who wrote the docket of P.Col. IV 122</note>
                     <note type="general">At the end of the letter there is an ornate paragraphos</note>
                     <textLang mainLang="grc">In Greek</textLang>
                  </msItemStruct>
